\pard\plain \ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 There is a rumor, circulated for centuries by scientists, artists, and philosohpers both secular and religious, a piece of gossip as it were, to the effect that women are \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93biologically conservative.\u8221\'94 While gossip among women is universally ridiculed as low and trivial, gossip among men, especially if it is about women, is called theory, or idea, or fact. This particular rumor became dignified as high thought because it was Whispered-Down-The_Lane in formidable academies, libraries, and meeting halls from which women, until very recently, mhave been formally and forcibly excluded.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 The whispers, however multisyllabic and footned they sometimes are, reduced to a simple enough set of assertions. Women have children because women because women by definition have children,. This \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93fact of life,\u8221\'94 whic his not subject to qualification, carries with it the instinctual obligation to nurture and protect those children. Therefore, women can be expected to be socially, politically, economically, and sexually conservative because the status quo, whatever it is, is safer than change, whatever the change. Noxious male philosophers from all disciplines have, for centuries, maintained htat women follow a biological imperative derived directly from their reproductive capacities that translates necessarily into narrow lives, small minds, and a rather meanspiriti3ed puritanism.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 This theory, or slander, is both specius iand cruel in that, in fact, women are forced to bear children and have been throughout history in all economic systems, with but teeny-weeny timeouts while men were momentarily disoriented, as for instance, in the immediate postcoital aftermath of certain revolutions. }
