\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Most girls do not want to become like their mothers, those tired, preoccupied domestic sergeants beset by incomoprehensible troubles. Mothers raise daughters to conform to the strictures of the conventional femal life as defined by men, whatever the ideoligcal values of the men. Mothers are the immediate envforcers of male will, the guards at the cell door, the flunkies who administer the electric shocks to punish rebellion.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Woman accept abuse in silence and shame, tie themselves to hearth and home with rope made of self-blame, unspoken rage, grief, and resentment.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 The lesbian is half monstor, half moron: having no man to nag, she imagines herself napoleon.}
